<AbstractNarration>This project from an EPSCoR state, developing a hardware-in-the-loop simulator (HILS) for mechatronic systems including robotics and hybrid electric vehicles, services 2 on-going projects and two new ones.&lt;br/&gt; Remotely controllable PUMA 560 Robot, &lt;br/&gt; Modeling and Simulation of HEV's,&lt;br/&gt; Remotely Controllable HILS for direct drive robot configuration, and &lt;br/&gt; Remotely Controllable HILS for geared robot configuration.&lt;br/&gt;The projects involve the remote control of an open architecture robot. PUMA, a staple learning robot, services introductory robotics.  The project allows and encourages conducting different remote experiments.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Broader Impact:  The platform services the wider Alaska community allowing hands-on work in courses that are currently limited to only theory, thus providing strong outreach educational opportunities.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
